	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=3823><span id= >nowalls</span></a><br><span id=notbold>44 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.83]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There are a couple reasons why these are nice boots for a necro.&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all, the 8 AC is pretty nice.  There are better boots out there, but 8 AC is nothing to complain about.  The extra 5 STR means that I will be able to carry more loot before I have to sell and bank.  This is huge when I'm soloing in a dungeon somewhere.  The extra STA and HP are good because necros are constantly trading HP for mana.  The more HP you have, the more mana you can get for it before you have to stop and steal HP from a mob to heal yourself.  The 5 mana the boots give isn't worth much, but free mana is always nice to have.<br><br>And then you get to the effect.  Scale of Wolf is a level 29 druid spell that is much faster than SoW.  The only problems with it are if you cast spells or enter melee combat, it disappears.  For a necro, I'm not so sure this is all that good for everyday use.  I like to run almost everywhere invis.  It's a habit I picked up after getting killed by a guard in EC at level 13.  I prefer getting a SoW and then just running invis.  I guess this would be nice if you get in trouble and need to get away fast.  Just target yourself, click the boots and run like a bard.<br><br>Sunil Grubsov<br>Iksar Necro (Level 26 Occultist)<br>Vazaelle<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
